researchResults.title: OpenAI reportedly finalizing $100B deal at more than $850B valuation
researchResults.description: OpenAI is reportedly getting close to closing a $100 billion deal, with backers including Amazon, Nvidia, SoftBank, and Microsoft. The deal would value the ChatGPT-maker at $850 billion.

researchResults.title: AI Impact Summit 2026
researchResults.description: A look at the partnerships and investments Google announced at the AI Impact Summit 2026.

researchResults.title: OpenAI, Reliance partner to add AI search to JioHotstar
researchResults.description: The rollout includes two-way integration that surfaces streaming links directly inside ChatGPT.

researchResults.title: Co-founders behind Reface and Prisma join hands to improve on-device model inference with Mirai
researchResults.description: Mirai raised a $10 million seed to improve how AI models run on devices like smartphones and laptops.

researchResults.title: For open-source programs, AI coding tools are a mixed blessing
researchResults.description: AI coding tools have enabled a flood of bad code that threatens to overwhelm many projects. Building new features is easier but maintaining them is just as hard.

researchResults.title: Altman and Amodei share a moment of awkwardness at India’s big AI summit
researchResults.description: When Prime Minister Narendra Modi prompted speakers at the event to join hands and raise them in a show of unity, all executives on stage obliged, except OpenAI's Sam Altman and Anthropic's Dario Amodei, who held their hands conspicuously apart.
